fields.description:
Kasabay ng pagdiriwang ng 14th Community Relations Service Month at sa ilalim ng  pamumuno ni JSUPT CHRISTOPHER R PENILLA, City Jail Warden, katuwang ang Department of Teacher Education ng Cavite State University ‚Äì Bacoor Campus sa pangunguna ni Ms. Jolina Razell M. Mindoro at ng kaniyang kapwa guro, isinagawa ang isang makabuluhang tutorial session na layuning palawakin ang kaalaman sa pagbasa at pagsulat ng mga Persons Deprived of Liberty (PDLs) sa Bacoor City Jail Male Dormitory. Ito ay isang hakbang tungo sa pagbubukas ng isipan, puso, at pag-asa para sa isang mas maliwanag na bukas.
Ang programang ito ay hindi lamang pagtuturo ng karunungan‚Äîito ay pagtuturo ng panibagong pananaw sa buhay, na sa kabila ng pagkakamali, may lugar pa rin para sa pagbabalik-loob, pag-unlad, at pagbangon.
Ito ay para sa mga PDL na hindi sapat ang kakayahan na bumasa at sumulat. Ngayon, unti-unti na nilang natututuhan ang mga kasanayang magagamit nila sa pagbabagong buhay.
BJMP Regional Office Calabarzon
City Government of Bacoor
PA Office Cavite Province
DepEd Bacoor City
Cavite State University - Bacoor City Campus

fields.title: "Closing the chapter with hope and wisdom."
fields.description:
On this day, June 18, 2025, marks our final tutoring and lecture session this quarter with the Persons Deprived of Liberty (PDLs). We end this journey filled with stories of growth, strength, and the power of learning.
In the pictures are the discussants, Ms. Crystalle Mae A. Genson Mr. Mathew Oliveros, and Mr. Kenn Pargan, with the tutors from the academic Department of Teacher Education.
We would also like to express our gratitude to Ma'am @Janette E. Alagar for helping us today.
#departmentofteachereducation

fields.title: PERFUME MAKING TRAINING AND BARISTA 101 GRADUATION CEREMONY üëè
fields.description:
The Bacoor City Jail Female Dormitory under the leadership of JSINSP SALLY C BUGUIS, Acting City Jail Warden, in partnership with Bacoorex Project 4: Kaagapay sa Kabuhayan Tungo sa Kaunlaran (KKK) of Cavite State University ‚Äì Bacoor Campus, successfully conducted the Graduation Ceremony for sixty (60) female Persons Deprived of Liberty (PDLs) who completed the Perfume Making Training and Barista 101. ‚òïüå∏
This milestone activity served not only as recognition of their perseverance and dedication, but also as a symbol of hope and new beginnings. Through these livelihood programs, the PDLs are equipped with valuable knowledge and practical skills that they can use for future opportunities, self-sufficiency, and smoother reintegration into the community. It also underscored the commitment of the Bureau of Jail Management and Penology (BJMP) to provide holistic and sustainable rehabilitation programs aimed at transforming PDLs into productive and responsible citizens.
The ceremony was graced by the presence of Ms. Janice A. Nealaga, MBA, Head of Campus Extension Services, together with trainers and instructors from Cavite State University ‚Äì Bacoor Campus, as well as personnel from the Bacoor City Jail Female Dormitory. Their participation highlighted the strong collaboration between the academe and the jail institution in advancing programs that support the rehabilitation and development of PDLs.
üëè Congratulations to our PDL graduates! Your hard work and determination serve as an inspiration that growth and change are always possible, even within the walls of the facility. üåü
City Government of Bacoor
BJMP Regional Office Calabarzon

fields.description:
Under the leadership of JSUPT CHRISTOPHER  R PENILLA, City Jail Warden, and JSINSP EDGARDO M PELAEZ, Assistant City Jail Warden, the Cavite State University (CAVSU)-Bacoor City Campus, led by Ms. Kathy J. Gumboc, Chairperson of the Department of Arts & Sciences, organized a heartwarming Family Fun Day for PDLs and their children as part of PROJECT SHINE.
This event brought together 50 PDLs, 60 children, and 43 guardians, assisted by BCJ-MD personnel JO1 Emily C Castro, Chief Welfare and Development Officer and JO1 Yvette C. Melgar, the GAD focal person/Project Shine Manager.
This event aims to maintain family bonds, provide emotional support, and foster a sense of connection, positively impacting the mental health and well-being of both PDLs and their children. Reuniting families helps reduce loneliness and builds a strong support system, which is essential for the reintegration process.

fields.description:
At Bacoor City Jail Male Dormitory (BCJMD), we are steadfast in our commitment to fostering positive transformation through our structured ‚Äú7-in-1 Activity‚Äù framework. This comprehensive program is carefully designed to address the multifaceted needs of Persons Deprived of Liberty (PDL), ensuring that they are well-equipped for a successful reintegration into society.
Today, April 3, 2025, BCJMD facilitated the following key activities aimed at enhancing the rehabilitation process for PDL:
1. Collaborative meeting with Cavite State University Bacoor Campus
2. Coordination meeting with DOST Cavite for Starbooks 
3. HIV and Syphillis Screening
4. Pre-release counselling for PDL
5. Random dorm search and security checks
6. Katatagan Kalusugan at Damayan ng Komunidad (KKDK) Session
7. Focused Support Services based on PDL needs
As modern jail officers, we play a key role in ensuring an environment that prioritizes security and supports personal growth and rehabilitation of PDL.

Yesterday, March 25,2025, under the leadership of JSUPT CHRISTOPHER R. PENILLA, City Jail Warden, the Bacoor City Jail-MD successfully hosted a skills training session focused on Bread and Pastry ‚Äì specifically, Vanilla Chiffon Cake Making. This session was conducted by Cavite State University-Bacoor Campus and attended by 30 Persons Deprived of Liberty (PDL).
This training is an important milestone in supporting the successful reintegration of PDLs into society. By providing them with essential culinary skills, the program not only enhances their self-esteem but also opens up pathways for future careers and business ventures. By fostering their abilities, we are helping to pave the way for a more promising and productive future, enabling them to make meaningful contributions to their communities.
